        <heading>3573.  Sequestration by court on its own motion</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 3573.  Sequestration by court on its own motion
The court on its own motion may order the sequestration of property the ownership of which is in dispute without requiring security when one of the parties does not appear to have a better right to possession than the other.</p>
        </content>
